## 1. High-Level Architecture

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Frontend (Vite + React)"
        UI["Spring2Fast UI"]
    end

    subgraph "FastAPI Backend"
        API["API Layer<br/>/api/v1/migrate"]
        ORC["MigrationOrchestrator"]
        GRAPH["LangGraph DAG"]
    end

    subgraph "LLM Providers"
        BDR["AWS Bedrock<br/>Llama 4 Maverick"]
        GRQ["Groq<br/>Llama 4 Scout"]
        GEM["Gemini Flash"]
    end

    subgraph "Persistence"
        SUPA["Supabase<br/>(Job tracking)"]
        FS["Filesystem<br/>(Workspace / Artifacts)"]
    end

    UI -->|"POST /github or /upload"| API
    UI -->|"GET /status, /state"| API
    API -->|"BackgroundTask"| ORC
    ORC -->|"ainvoke / astream"| GRAPH
    GRAPH -->|"LLM calls"| BDR
    GRAPH -.->|"fallback"| GRQ
    GRAPH -.->|"fallback"| GEM
    ORC -->|"persist state"| FS
    ORC -->|"update progress"| SUPA
    API -->|"query jobs"| SUPA
```

The system is split into three layers:
- **API Layer** — FastAPI endpoints that accept migration requests and serve status/results
- **Orchestration Layer** — Thin wrapper that initializes state, streams the graph, and persists progress
- **Agent Layer** — A LangGraph DAG with 11 nodes + an embedded supervisor subgraph for the actual code conversion

