## 2. API & Orchestration Layer

### API Endpoints — [migrate.py](file:///c:/Users/Musharraf/Documents/Gen-AI/spring2fast/app/api/v1/migrate.py)

| Endpoint | Method | Purpose |
|----------|--------|---------|
| `/github` | POST | Start migration from a GitHub repo URL |
| `/upload` | POST | Start migration from an uploaded ZIP |
| `/{job_id}/status` | GET | Quick status + progress percentage |
| `/{job_id}/state` | GET | Full state dump (logs, artifacts, conversions) |
| `/{job_id}/result` | GET | Download the output ZIP |
| `/{job_id}/artifacts` | GET | List all generated analysis artifacts |
| `/{job_id}/source-tree` | GET | File tree of ingested Java source |
| `/{job_id}/output-tree` | GET | File tree of generated Python output |
| `/{job_id}/push-github` | POST | Push output to a new GitHub repo |
| `/{job_id}/sandbox` | POST | Run live smoke tests on the generated app |

### Orchestrator — [migration_orchestrator.py](file:///c:/Users/Musharraf/Documents/Gen-AI/spring2fast/app/services/migration_orchestrator.py)

The `MigrationOrchestrator` is intentionally thin:

1. Builds the compiled LangGraph with `build_migration_graph()`
2. Constructs the `initial_state` dict with job metadata
3. Streams the graph via `astream(state, stream_mode="values")`
4. After each node completion:
   - Persists state to `_state.json` (for frontend polling)
   - Updates Supabase `migration_jobs` table (status, progress_pct, current_step)
5. On error: marks the job as `failed` in Supabase
6. On success: records output ZIP path and `completed_at` timestamp

