## 3. LangGraph DAG — The Main Graph

[graph.py](file:///c:/Users/Musharraf/Documents/Gen-AI/spring2fast/app/agents/graph.py)

```
                     ┌── tech_discover ──────────┐
     ingest ─────────┼── biz_logic ──────────────┼── merge_analysis
                     └── discover_components ────┘          │
                                                            ▼
                                                 research_docs → analyze → plan
                                                            │
                                               ┌────────────▼──────────────┐
                                               │  MIGRATION SUBGRAPH       │
                                               │  supervisor → converters  │
                                               │  → quality_gate → exit    │
                                               └────────────┬──────────────┘
                                                            │
                                                 validate ─┬─ always → assemble → END
```

### 11 Registered Nodes

| Node | Type | Purpose |
|------|------|---------|
| `ingest` | sync | Clone repo / extract ZIP / copy folder into workspace |
| `tech_discover` | async | Scan for Java technologies (Spring Security, JPA, Kafka, etc.) |
| `extract_business_logic` | async | LLM-enriched extraction of business rules from service classes |
| `discover_components` | sync | Regex-based classification of all Java classes + contract generation |
| `merge_analysis` | sync | Fan-in checkpoint — cross-references parallel analysis results |
| `research_docs` | async | Maps Java techs to official Python lib documentation (Serper/MCP) |
| `analyze` | sync | Architecture dependency analysis |
| `plan` | async | LLM-powered migration plan + builds the conversion queue |
| `migrate` | **subgraph** | Supervisor+converter agents (see §6) |
| `validate` | async | 6-layer validation of generated code |
| `assemble` | sync | Infrastructure scaffolding, Docker, Alembic, tests, ZIP packaging |

### Edge Wiring

- **Fan-out**: `ingest` → `[tech_discover, extract_business_logic, discover_components]` (parallel)
- **Fan-in**: All three → `merge_analysis` (LangGraph reducers merge state)
- **Sequential**: `merge_analysis` → `research_docs` → `analyze` → `plan` → `migrate` → `validate` → `assemble` → END
- `validate` always routes to `assemble` (no retry loops at the outer level)

