## 4. Shared State Schema (`MigrationState`)

[state.py](file:///c:/Users/Musharraf/Documents/Gen-AI/spring2fast/app/agents/state.py)

The state is a `TypedDict` with **Annotated reducers** that tell LangGraph how to merge partial state updates from parallel branches:

| Field | Reducer | Purpose |
|-------|---------|---------|
| `job_id`, `source_url`, `workspace_dir` | `_latest_any` | Identity fields (set once) |
| `status`, `current_step` | `_latest_str` | Human-readable progress |
| `progress_pct` | `_latest_int` (max) | Always takes the highest value |
| `logs` | `_dedupe_list` | Concatenate + deduplicate across branches |
| `discovered_technologies`, `business_rules`, `generated_files` | `_dedupe_list` | Merge collections from parallel nodes |
| `analysis_artifacts`, `metadata` | `_merge_dicts` | Deep-merge nested dicts |
| `component_inventory` | `_merge_dicts` | Structured component registry |
| `conversion_queue`, `completed_conversions`, `failed_conversions`, `current_conversion` | **`_always_latest`** | Supervisor signal fields — `None`/`[]` are meaningful |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The supervisor subgraph fields use `_always_latest` (not `_latest_any`) because `None` and `[]` are meaningful signals. Using `_latest_any` would silently keep stale values and cause the supervisor loop to never exit.

