## 6. Migration Subgraph — The Supervisor Pattern

[migration_subgraph/graph.py](file:///c:/Users/Musharraf/Documents/Gen-AI/spring2fast/app/agents/migration_subgraph/graph.py)

The `migrate` node in the main DAG is actually a **compiled subgraph**:

```mermaid
graph LR
    SUP["supervisor"] -->|"route"| MC["model_converter"]
    SUP -->|"route"| SC["schema_converter"]
    SUP -->|"route"| RC["repo_converter"]
    SUP -->|"route"| SVC["service_converter"]
    SUP -->|"route"| CC["controller_converter"]
    SUP -->|"route"| EC["exception_converter"]
    SUP -->|"route"| FC["feign_converter"]
    SUP -->|"route"| ECC["event_consumer_converter"]
    SUP -->|"route"| SKC["scheduler_converter"]
    SUP -->|"route"| CFG["config_converter"]
    SUP -->|"queue empty"| QG["quality_gate"]
    
    MC --> SUP
    SC --> SUP
    RC --> SUP
    SVC --> SUP
    CC --> SUP
    EC --> SUP
    FC --> SUP
    ECC --> SUP
    SKC --> SUP
    CFG --> SUP
    
    QG -->|"exit"| END["END"]
    QG -->|"retry"| SUP
```

### Supervisor — [supervisor.py](file:///c:/Users/Musharraf/Documents/Gen-AI/spring2fast/app/agents/migration_subgraph/supervisor.py)

The supervisor is a **pure function** (not an LLM agent). Each invocation:
1. Pops the next component from `conversion_queue`
2. Sets `current_conversion` to that component
3. Reads already-generated code from the output directory (for cross-layer context)
4. Routes deterministically via `route_to_converter()` based on component type

### Quality Gate — [quality_gate.py](file:///c:/Users/Musharraf/Documents/Gen-AI/spring2fast/app/agents/migration_subgraph/quality_gate.py)

Triggered when the queue is empty. It:
- Counts passed/failed conversions
- If failures exist and `retry_count < 2`: re-queues failed components, increments retry counter, routes back to supervisor
- If all passed or retries exhausted: exits the subgraph

