## 8. LLM Routing & Model Strategy

[core/llm.py](file:///c:/Users/Musharraf/Documents/Gen-AI/spring2fast/app/core/llm.py)

```
┌─────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────┐
│ Task                    │ Model                        │ Why                        │
├─────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────┤
│ Code generation         │ Bedrock Llama 4 Maverick     │ No RPM limits, strong code │
│ Analysis / Planning     │ Bedrock → Groq → Gemini      │ Safe for parallel nodes    │
└─────────────────────────┴──────────────────────────────┴────────────────────────────┘
```

**Fallback chain**: Bedrock → Groq Llama 4 Scout → Gemini 2.0 Flash

> [!NOTE]
> Bedrock is preferred over Groq because 3 parallel analysis nodes all fire LLM calls simultaneously. Groq's free tier (30 RPM) would 429 instantly. Bedrock has no RPM cap (pay-per-token).

When neither Bedrock nor Groq is available, the code LLM is `None` — converter agents fall back to generating **TODO scaffold** files (valid Python with stub methods).

A 3-second throttle is applied between converter agent calls when using Groq to stay under the 30 RPM limit.

