## 9. Validation & Quality Assurance

[validation_service.py](file:///c:/Users/Musharraf/Documents/Gen-AI/spring2fast/app/services/validation_service.py)

The validation node runs 6 checks on the generated output:

| # | Check | Method | Severity |
|---|-------|--------|----------|
| 1 | **Syntax** | `ast.parse()` on every `.py` file | Fatal |
| 2 | **Lint** | `ruff check --select=E,F,I` | F-errors fatal, E-warnings non-fatal |
| 3 | **Import resolution** | Checks every `from app.` import against generated module index + stdlib + requirements.txt | Fatal |
| 4 | **Structural integrity** | Every entity/service/controller/repo in inventory has a matching generated file | Fatal |
| 5 | **Core files** | `app/main.py` and `requirements.txt` must exist | Fatal |
| 6 | **Contract compliance** | LLM-as-judge: generated code is checked against business logic contracts | Fatal |

Writes `08-validation-report.md` with a checks summary table.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Validation **never blocks** the pipeline. Errors are logged and the pipeline always proceeds to assembly. The design philosophy: deliver ALL migrated code, even if imperfect — the user can manually fix issues.

