## 13. Key Design Decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|----------|-----------|
| **Supervisor is a pure function, not an LLM agent** | Routing is deterministic by component type — no need to waste LLM calls on routing decisions |
| **Inner validation loop in converter agents** | Catches ~80% of issues cheaply before the expensive quality gate retry |
| **Stub method detection forces LLM retry** | LLMs sometimes generate syntactically valid but functionally empty code; AST-walking detects this |
| **`_always_latest` reducer for subgraph fields** | `None`/`[]` are meaningful exit signals; `_latest_any` would silently ignore them |
| **Bedrock-first LLM routing** | Eliminates rate-limit issues during parallel analysis and dense conversion phases |
| **Validation never blocks assembly** | Philosophy: deliver all code, report issues; user manually fixes. Re-migration loops proved brittle |
| **Business logic contracts** | Structured `.md` files are more reliable than flat rules lists for LLM synthesis context |
| **Dependency-ordered conversion queue** | Models before schemas before repos before services before controllers — ensures cross-layer imports resolve |

